Cookie policy We explain what cookies are, how Alamy use them and how you can manage or remove them.
What are cookies? A cookie is a small file stored on your device that's created each time you visit a website.
Multiple cookies can be stored from one website and are used to make your online experience easier.
A cookie file is generated by the site you're browsing and is accepted and processed by your computer's browser software.
The cookie file is stored in your browser's local folder or subfolder.
Cookies save your browsing information which means sites can keep you signed in, remember your site preferences, and give you locally relevant content.
What sort of cookies does the Alamy website use?
Cookies help us improve your experience by providing us with information about how the website is being used.
Our cookies do not store financial information or other personal information such as your name or email address.
In addition to our own cookies, we use third party tools which also use cookies.
There is a notice on our website which provides a link to our cookie policy.
If you continue to use the Alamy website, we will assume your consent to the use of cookies for this purpose.
If, after reading this information you have any questions or concerns about our cookie policy please contact us at sales@alamy.com or read our privacy policy.

Strictly Necessary These cookies are essential for the operation of our websites.
For example, they keep track of what you have in your basket and identify you as being logged in to the website and allows us to recognise you as a customer or contributor.
If you block these cookies we cannot guarantee the website will perform correctly.
Performance We use these cookies to analyse how our visitors use our websites and to monitor website performance.
For example, we might use them to keep track of which pages are most popular, test new website's design and operability and to see why some pages are receiving error messages.
Functionality We use functionality cookies to remember choices you make such as which regional edition of the website you want to see when you log in.
These cookies recall any customisation you make to pages on the website during your visit.
If you block these cookies certain features and services may be affected and we cannot be sure how the Website will perform during your visit.
Marketing These cookies are used to track our visitors browsing habits and activity across our websites.
They can be used to build up a profile of search and/or browsing history for every visitor.
Identifiable or unique data may be collected. Anonymized data may be shared with third parties.
This information is linked to site functionality provided by other websites, and may be shared with other organisations (such as advertising networks).
Third party We also use or allow third parties to serve cookies that fall into the four categories above.
For example, like many companies, we use Google Analytics to help us monitor our website traffic.
We may also use third party cookies to help us with market research, revenue tracking, improving site functionality and monitoring compliance with our terms and conditions.
How do I control my cookies? You can manage the cookies we store from you on our website through your internet browser settings at any time.
For more information about how to do this, and about cookies in general, you can visit https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/online/cookies/ and http://www.youronlinechoices.eu
Please be aware that if you turn off all cookies, your experience on our website will be impacted, some of the functionality will be reduced and your overall experience on Alamy will be poorer.
In this policy you will find all the information you need about our cookies usage.
If you feel uncomfortable with these cookies, please ask us for more info or use the above guidelines to turn them off.
